# Schmeet - OpenGL Game

A simple OpenGL game project built with C++ and modern graphics libraries.

## Libraries Used

### Core Graphics Libraries
- **OpenGL** - Graphics rendering API
- **GLFW 3.4** - Window management and input handling
- **GLAD** - OpenGL function loader (loads OpenGL functions at runtime)

### System Libraries
- **OpenGL32** - Windows OpenGL implementation
- **GDI32** - Graphics Device Interface (Windows)
- **User32** - Windows user interface functions
- **Kernel32** - Windows kernel functions

## Project Structure

```
Game/
├── build/                    # Build output directory
│   ├── main.exe             # Compiled executable
│   └── glfw3.dll            # GLFW runtime library
├── src/                     # Source code
│   ├── main.cpp             # Main application code
│   └── glad.c               # GLAD OpenGL loader
├── include/                 # Header files
│   ├── GLFW/                # GLFW headers
│   └── glad/                # GLAD headers
├── lib/                     # Library files
│   └── libglfw3dll.a        # GLFW static library
├── .vscode/                 # VS Code/Cursor configuration
│   ├── tasks.json           # Build tasks
│   ├── launch.json          # Debug configuration
│   └── c_cpp_properties.json # IntelliSense settings
└── glfw3.dll                # GLFW runtime library (root)
```

## Requirements

- **Compiler**: GCC 15.x or newer (MinGW-w64 recommended)
- **Operating System**: Windows 10/11
- **Graphics**: OpenGL 3.3 compatible graphics card

## How to Run

1. Open the project in VS Code or Cursor
2. Press `Ctrl+Shift+B` to build the project
3. Press `Ctrl+Shift+P` → "Tasks: Run Task" → "Run OpenGL Project"

## Controls

- **ESC** - Close the application (when implemented)
- **Window Resize** - Automatically adjusts viewport
